For this problem, we will first utilize the present value annuity which is basically the current value of future payments done per interval based on a given rate. This can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Present value}&=\dfrac{\text{Cash flow}}{(1+\text{rate})^\text{time}}
\end{aligned}$$

Now that we have the present value for Year 3, we can now solve for its future value to solve for the missing cash flow. The future value can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Future value}&=\text{Cash flow} \times (1+\text{rate})^\text{time}
\end{aligned}$$
